body:
Ah, right, `==` and `!=` aren't overloaded.
In this case, would it make more sense to extend `testTensorCompareTensor` and friends?
(Which also test `tf.equal` and `tf.not_equal`, but don't contain `complex64` and `complex128` at the moment)

**edit:** Ah, `testTensorCompareTensor` also already tests for `complex64` at the bottom
